<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1002</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-10T15:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 10, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1208. Urgent. Your 2190, December 7, 2 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d386fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_461">p.
                                    461</ref>.</note> If <persName corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName> left before receipt of Department’s 1200 of
                                December 7, 5 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d386fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_458">p.
                                    458</ref>.</note> hold <pb facs="0541" n="467" xml:id="pg_467"/>
                                him at the border if possible and if he has crossed endeavor to
                                instruct him to return at once.</p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName>’s mission was to
                                obtain information regarding political conditions, particularly
                                constitutional reforms in the Central Empires. He has exceeded his
                                authority and failed to comply with explicit instructions that he
                                was not to enter enemy territory without obtaining permission.</p>
                            <p>If you think it desirable, advise your British and French colleagues
                                confidentially of the foregoing and disavow absolutely <persName corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName>’s action.</p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName> should proceed as
                                soon as possible to London. Please expedite his departure.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>